{"hash":"390d302cd552305fd677e06bbdca7834a7d72d7b","data":{"post":{"title":"Gridsome v0.5","date":"19. February 2019","timeToRead":3,"content":"<h2 id=\"filtering-graphql-data\"><a href=\"#filtering-graphql-data\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Filtering GraphQL data</h2>\n<p>Each content type collection in the GraphQL schema has a new <code class=\"language-text\">filter</code> argument which can be used to filter the results. You can filter by <code class=\"language-text\">id</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">title</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">slug</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">path</code> or any custom field.</p>\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"/docs/filtering-data/\">Filtering data</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"create-taxonomy-pages\"><a href=\"#create-taxonomy-pages\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Create taxonomy pages</h2>\n<p>All references in the GraphQL schema has been a one-way relation. This release introduces a new field called <code class=\"language-text\">belongsTo</code> for all content types. The field will list all nodes that have a reference back to the current node which makes it very useful to create taxonomy pages etc. The field can also take the same arguments as a collection. And the <code class=\"language-text\">@paginate</code> directive can be used to automatically paginate the results.</p>\n<p>For example, this can be used to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>List blog posts for an author.</li>\n<li>List posts for a tag or category.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We're using this feature on <strong>Gridsome blog</strong> for the <strong>authors</strong>. The authors here are just a YAML file that lists authors, and then Gridsome magically connects it all.</p>\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"/docs/taxonomies/\">Taxonomies</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"variables-in-page-query\"><a href=\"#variables-in-page-query\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Variables in Page Query</h2>\n<p>Previously, only <code class=\"language-text\">$path</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">$page</code> were available as variables for <code class=\"language-text\">page-query</code> in templates. But you can now use <code class=\"language-text\">$id</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">$title</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">$slug</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">$date</code> or any custom field from the current <code class=\"language-text\">node</code>. Deep objects and arrays can also be used as variables.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$id</code> resolves to <code class=\"language-text\">node.id</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$value</code> resolves to <code class=\"language-text\">node.fields.value</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$object__value</code> resolves to <code class=\"language-text\">node.fields.object.value</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$array__3__id</code> resolves to <code class=\"language-text\">node.fields.array[3].id</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"/docs/querying-data/#query-data-in-templates\">Query data in templates</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"environment-variables\"><a href=\"#environment-variables\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Environment variables</h2>\n<p>Sometimes you want configuration values that are different from what you have in the production build. Gridsome now utilizes the <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">dotenv</a> package to make this easy. Special thanks to <a href=\"https://github.com/isoppp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">isoppp</a> for implementing this feature ðŸ˜„</p>\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"/docs/environment-variables/\">Environment Variables</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"new-plugin-library\"><a href=\"#new-plugin-library\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>New Plugin library</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/plugins/\">Plugins</a> page now gets plugins from NPM directory. Any plugin with keyword <code class=\"language-text\">gridsome-plugin</code> will be listed here. You can also use the search field for filtering.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1752 1150' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-2ac1abf0320dd9cbf909f18587b575d0'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-2ac1abf0320dd9cbf909f18587b575d0)' width='1752' height='1150' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAqCAYAAAADBl3iAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAALXElEQVRo3uVaaZBU1RW%2bDQ0JhDUKArI2AWRYRDAyiksUwloVy8TIbkkpi8BAUiBioglJQJaUf5zCEq3KryxVqZIIyhZFi8UgUsQNmBkQmB2YfWCmp3v6vXdyvtPv9rx%2b/Xrm9UiqTHxVp%2b767jvn3O8s93ar8rIytfP1N9W37YHMTU1NSv35r39Tw4cNCXQfemf/7kPGD%2b82ZFwo0GlQSHVlCt4aUh1vCanOfbm8NdSx74jQ9waNDaleQ0Od%2bo0KdbptZEh1GxhSXfqHglwHqd7DQl1uzwp153W6DY5TS31sCOt3c4wJDYnPic8b63on3tdj6PiQuiUUUqpnSAV6c9krpDr1iX%2b/A/PYfWB8vOfgkOoxqKXO/KheQ4Tf%2bDfGD%2b8x9M4BoSGDArv/8bZSjz6xUHVVqmOvUdlHeo%2beQr1GZjcPeHCGMXDyj40R9842hmfPNIbeM90ITZ5h9B37oNH7jnuNAXf%2byOgz5n6mB4yBE6cag%2b%2beZvQZ%2b4C0%2b/PYLaOnGL1G3Wv0vonUc2S2MWjSNGPC1J8Z4x5%2bzBj/yE%2bNMQ89aoy8bw7XH2NeZxn9xj9kDJjwsDGY54EP8IY2CPwyT80i46js099lmR/9%2bXyl7po8RXXtqDqrflkfqQHjSd2WZXZ7aCr1mTKNJk59nCbPnk/3zJpHd8%2bYS73vuI8C/ccSL0w9RkymLsMm0fDsWTTivtnUndvdfzCZ%2bGPUadAErEOK56p%2bY74%2bYZ2%2bo4kVTNlzFtDE6U8IP6wMGnbPTLpr2uM07IfT6fssXN9xDwp/t2bdT7ff9YiUvDnUZegkrGWqAeNQft61g%2bp8d/aUgJo55ycBNonvrH5h8/H1v3%2bF1ry4NZbzqy0WaNULm62VTFJu/IOV8%2buXLR63VvPYGq6jvdqel2O35V173s2mtS9tc9BW6xe/2Wb98rfbpQSBF02aN2eb1zDW/e4VYh4/g8wzZs0JqDVrckQBRHSc4o9B/7%2bPlk0UsHjRooBavny5KCAcbhIFGPxEos3U1BRJonBTEzVFIhTFGJeRSJSaYzGKxQyh5uaYjEmd%2b3mZm0axm7eWKID5FwXMnTs3oFatWiUKiEajCQRAiOqaGqqtraXr168L1XC7qqpK%2bjBWXV1N9npkK46V0EyW